	<br><b>NFL DRAFT RULES</b>
	
	<TABLE align="center" WIDTH="100%" CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=4 BORDER=0>

		<tr>
		  <td align="center">
		    The NFL Draft order is determined by the reverse order of each teams finish that season.  <br/>
		    The teams that do not qualify for the playoffs are assigned picks 1 through 18.  <br/>
		    Teams reaching the playoffs are assigned picks 19 through 32 based on their postseason finish. <br/>
			The six teams eliminated in the Wild Card round will be assigned picks 19-24 based on regular season record.  <br/>
			The four teams eliminated in the Divisional round will be assigned picks 25-28 based on regular season record.  <br/>
			The two teams eliminated in the Conference Championships will be assigned picks 29 and 30 based on regular season record.  <br/>
			The team that loses the Super Bowl will be assigned pick 31.  <br/>
			The Super Bowl champion will be assigned pick 32.  <br/>
		  </td>
		</tr> 	
	
	</table>

